@neil_tijerina @MattDav00282166 @SpenceCunninton With all due respect, you thinking a leadoff hitter needs to be fast is an extremely obsolete mindset in baseball. That way of thinking disappeared years ago
@neil_tijerina @MattDav00282166 @SpenceCunninton Harrison swings at every single pitch he sees. He's #24 on the list of who shouldn't be leading off, right after McGuire at #23

Shohei Ohtani should be inching close to like... lebron level in popularity in pop culture, but I don't feel like he is. What he's doing hasn't been done in 100 years and won't be done for another 100 years. MLB's really screwing the pooch there, which should shock nobody at all

@neil_tijerina @MattDav00282166 @SpenceCunninton There were 4 in house options that could do not just what LG does, but way MORE than what he does. Those guys all would be making $700K to LGs $5MM. Those same guys should be given shots now. We know what Garcia is; bad. Find out what the others are and spend LG's money elsewhere

@neil_tijerina @MattDav00282166 @SpenceCunninton Then let's circle back on this next time TA needs a breather 

And the same basically goes for if he automatically inserts JH to leadoff too, though he's had success over his career and looks good the last 1-2 weeks. The lineup should literally just be shifted up 1 when ppl rest

@neil_tijerina @MattDav00282166 @SpenceCunninton And TA will need breathers. Garcia should be the absolute dead last option to replace him at leadoff. If he hits 9th and plays SS here and there, whatever, but he doesn't. He's counted on too frequently in high leverage plate appearances and that hurts the sox chances of winning

@neil_tijerina @MattDav00282166 @SpenceCunninton I lied, 11th worst over the last 10 years min. 2000 plate appearances

There is absolutely no reason for him to play as much as he does. This team says they are contending https://t.co/7aOhVpv1Xc

@neil_tijerina @MattDav00282166 @SpenceCunninton Getting guys like Abreu, Moncada, Vaughn, and the others who were underperforming at bats was necessary because those guys have a history of a TON of success. Garcia doesn't. In fact, he's the worst player to have 2000 plate appearances in the last 10 years

@neil_tijerina @MattDav00282166 @SpenceCunninton What about Leury hitting 3rd?

And a team can't simultaneously say they are putting their best foot forward on trying to win a World Series while simultaneously "needing" Leury Garcia... yet he plays almost regularly and not because they "need" him to
